  "prompt": "Who was Billy the Kid and why is he famous?",
  "response": "Billy the Kid, born Henry McCarty (also known as William H. Bonney), was a famous Wild West outlaw who lived from 1859 to 1881. He is primarily known for:\n\n1. Being a notorious gunslinger in the American Southwest, particularly in New Mexico Territory\n\n2. Participating in the Lincoln County War, a violent conflict between rival business factions in New Mexico\n\n3. Allegedly killing 21 men (though some historians dispute this number)\n\n4. Being pursued by Sheriff Pat Garrett, who eventually killed Billy the Kid in 1881\n\n5. Becoming a legendary figure in American folklore and Wild West mythology\n\nBilly the Kid was a charismatic and controversial figure who became famous for his perceived rebelliousness, skill with firearms, and ability to escape capture. Despite his criminal activities, he was sometimes viewed sympathetically by locals as a young man caught up in difficult circumstances.\n\nHis life was relatively short - he was killed at age 21 by Sheriff Pat Garrett - but his legend has endured in American popular culture through numerous books, movies, and historical accounts. He represents a romanticized image of the lawless frontier and the complex moral landscape of the American West during the late 19th century.",
